1. Track a high score that persists across scenes and display it in the UI (5)

  This can be found on the upper of the screen, marked as high.

2. Implement the 'FIRE' UI text from the original game (5)
  
  when the rocket is fired, there will be an indicator for the flying of the rocket.

3. Add your own (copyright-free) background music to the Play scene (5)

   the music is added in the play scene, and it is copy right free
  
4. Implement the speed increase that happens after 30 seconds in the original game (5)

  after 30 second, the speed of the ship will change.

5. Allow the player to control the Rocket after it's fired (5)

  both of the play will be able to control the rockets after they are fired.

6. Create 4 new explosion SFX and randomize which one plays on impact (10)

  try to hit the rocket multiple times, and the player will hear 4 different explosion fx.

7. Display the time remaining (in seconds) on the screen (10)

  the remaining time will be display on the upper screen, and it counts down.

8. Implement a new timing/scoring mechanism that adds time to the clock for successful hits (20)

  when hitting different ships, the amount of time added is different, too. there is a small console lable on the lower screen
  it indicates how much time the player gets when he/she hits a target.

9. Implement simultaneous 2 player mode (30)

  The player(s) can choose whether to play in single mode or two players mode
  p1 uses <->, p2 uses A/D for movement, p1 uses 'F' to fire, p2 uses 'G' to fire

10. a new cover for the menu page

  a new artwork cover is added for the menu scene, though it is rather a make-shift one.
